The paper deals with the problem of generating a novel image by manipulating two input images, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method uses GANs, which are widely used in computer vision and machine learning. The paper also introduces a novel training method called Min-Patch training, which is a new approach to focus the generator on crucial parts of an image. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also deals with unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning, so cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new method for training GANs, which is a topic in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to generating images, which is a topic in artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category.
